---
import Layout from '../../layouts/LayoutCore.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'January 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="BudgetBaby Terms of Use"
  description="BudgetBaby Terms of Use: usage, subscriptions, limitations, and contact information."
  canonical="/budgetbaby/terms"
>
  <div class="policy-layout">
    <div class="container-sm">
      <div class="policy-header">
        <a href="/budgetbaby" class="policy-back">← BudgetBaby</a>
        <div class="label-chip" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">Legal</div>
        <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="policy-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated} · Applies to BudgetBaby for iOS</p>
        <p class="policy-summary">
          These Terms of Use govern your use of BudgetBaby. By downloading or using the app,
          you agree to these terms. We've kept them as clear and jargon-free as possible.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-content">

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2>1. About BudgetBaby</h2>
          <p>
            BudgetBaby is a personal finance tracking application published by <strong>Intrigue MMC LLC</strong>,
            operating as Intriguing Insight ("we," "us," "our"). The app is available for iOS 17.0 and later.
          </p>
          <p>
            BudgetBaby is a personal finance tool. It is not a bank, financial institution, investment adviser,
            or financial planner. Nothing in the app or on this site constitutes financial advice.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2>2. Acceptable use</h2>
          <p>You may use BudgetBaby for your personal, non-commercial budget tracking. You agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the app.</li>
            <li>Use the app in any unlawful manner or for any unlawful purpose.</li>
            <li>Attempt to circumvent or disable any security features, including premium access controls.</li>
            <li>Share your account credentials with others or allow others to use your account.</li>
            <li>Use the app to process data on behalf of others as a service without our written consent.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2>3. Subscriptions</h2>
          <h3>Premium subscription</h3>
          <p>
            BudgetBaby Premium is available as a monthly ($4.99/month) or annual ($39.99/year) auto-renewing subscription,
            purchased through the Apple App Store.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Subscriptions automatically renew unless cancelled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.</li>
            <li>You can manage and cancel your subscription in iOS Settings → [Your Name] → Subscriptions.</li>
            <li>Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period. No refunds are issued for unused portions of a subscription period unless required by applicable law.</li>
            <li>Prices are stated in USD and may vary by region according to App Store pricing.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Free tier</h3>
          <p>
            The free tier of BudgetBaby is fully functional for core budgeting. Free tier limits are documented
            in the app and on the <a href="/budgetbaby/features">Features page</a>. We reserve the right to
            adjust free tier limits with reasonable notice.
          </p>

          <h3>Refunds</h3>
          <p>
            Subscription purchases are processed by Apple. Refund requests must be submitted to Apple directly
            at <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">reportaproblem.apple.com</a>.
            We cannot issue refunds directly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2>4. Your data</h2>
          <p>You own your data. We do not claim any rights to your budget data, transactions, or financial information.</p>
          <p>
            Local data stored on your device is yours entirely. Cloud backup data is encrypted on your device
            before upload and we cannot read it. For full details, see our <a href="/budgetbaby/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            You are responsible for maintaining backups of your data. We are not liable for data loss caused by
            device failure, app uninstallation, or other circumstances outside our control.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2>5. Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p>
            BudgetBaby is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, either express or implied.
            We do not warrant that the app will be uninterrupted, error-free, or completely accurate.
          </p>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Intrigue MMC LLC is not liable for:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Any financial decisions made based on information displayed in the app.</li>
            <li>Loss of data due to device failure, app bugs, or user error.</li>
            <li>Any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of the app.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            If you are dissatisfied with the app, your sole remedy is to discontinue use.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2>6. Intellectual property</h2>
          <p>
            BudgetBaby, including its design, code, and content, is owned by Intrigue MMC LLC.
            All rights reserved. The BabyBlocks name and related marks are trademarks of Intrigue MMC LLC.
          </p>
          <p>
            Nothing in these Terms grants you any right to use our trademarks, logos, or brand assets
            without prior written consent.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2>7. Changes to the app and terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update BudgetBaby and these Terms from time to time. Material changes to Terms will be
            communicated via an in-app notice. Your continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.
          </p>
          <p>
            We may discontinue features, change pricing, or modify the free tier limits with reasonable advance notice.
            We will not retroactively revoke access to features you have already paid for within a current billing period.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2>8. Governing law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Delaware, United States, applicable to contracts
            made and performed entirely within that jurisdiction, without regard to conflict of law principles.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2>9. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about these Terms? Contact us at <a href="mailto:support@babyblocks.io">support@babyblocks.io</a>.<br />
            <strong>Intrigue MMC LLC</strong> · operating as Intriguing Insight
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .policy-layout {
    padding-top: calc(var(--nav-height) + var(--space-12));
    padding-bottom: var(--space-24);
  }

  .policy-back {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-block;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }
  .policy-back:hover { color: var(--text-secondary); }

  .policy-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-8);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
  }

  .policy-header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(var(--text-3xl), 5vw, var(--text-5xl));
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .policy-meta {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .policy-summary {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }

  .policy-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-10);
  }

  .policy-section h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .policy-section h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    margin-top: var(--space-5);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .policy-section p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .policy-section p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .policy-section ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-block: var(--space-3);
  }
</style>
